<div id="pf21" class="pf w2 h0" data-page-no="21"><div class="pc pc21 w2 h0"><img class="bi x0 y0 w3 h1" alt="" src="bg21.png"/><div class="t m0 x3c h1f y24e ff11 fs19 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">32</div><div class="t m16 x63 h38 y4c9 ff26 fs28 fc1 sc0 ls2 ws5">M<span class="_ _1"></span><span class="ff27 fs29">o<span class="_ _1"></span>n<span class="_ _1"></span>d<span class="_ _1"></span>a<span class="_ _1"></span>y</span></div><div class="t m17 x15 h30 y2a9 ff11 fs24 fc3 sc0 ls12 ws5c">January 21</div><div class="t m0 x46 h39 y2aa ff13 fs2a fc3 sc0 ls13 ws5d">Creation in the Psalms</div><div class="t m15 x3c h33 y2ab ff14 fs19 fc6 sc0 ls2 ws5">Read</div><div class="t m0 x5c h35 y2ab ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6"> Psalm 8. What links do you find with Genesis 1? </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4ca ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">___<span class="_ _4"></span>___<span class="_ _9"></span>_<span class="_ _9"></span>_________________________________________________</div><div class="t m15 x3c h33 y4cb ff14 fs19 fc6 sc0 ls2 ws5">Read</div><div class="t m0 x5c h35 y4cb ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws55"> Psalm 104. Note how this psalm praises God for His goodness </div><div class="t m0 x46 h35 y4cc ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsd3">as seen in both Creation and providence. Identify the links with </div><div class="t m0 x46 h35 y4cd ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Genesis 1 in the following verses from Psalm 104:</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4ce ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vs. 2___________________________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4cf ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d0 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vss. 5–7________________________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d1 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d2 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vss. 7–9________________________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d3 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d4 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vs. 14__________________________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d5 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d6 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vs. 19__________________________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d7 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4d8 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Vs. 25__________________________________________________ </div><div class="t m0 x59 h37 y4d9 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws127">Note how the psalm’s topical sequence seems to be crafted to </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4da ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws8d">follow the topical sequence of Genesis 1. Poetic imagery is vividly </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4db ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wse8">presented throughout the verses, and its message clearly includes the </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4dc ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsda">power, wisdom, and goodness of God and the dependence of all the </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4dd ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws58">Creation on the Creator. Nothing in the psalm hints that the Genesis </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4de ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">account was not to be taken literally.</div><div class="t m15 x3c h33 y4df ff14 fs19 fc6 sc0 ls2 ws5">Note</div><div class="t m0 x6c h35 y4df ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws10c"> the following examples from the Psalms that correlate with </div><div class="t m0 x46 h35 y4e0 ff13 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Genesis 1.</div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e1 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Ps. 24:1, 2_______________________________________________ </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e2 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Ps. 33:6_________________________________________________ </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e3 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Ps. 74:16, 17_____________________________________________ </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e4 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Ps. 89:11________________________________________________ </div><div class="t m0 x59 h37 y4e5 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wsff">The Psalms are full of praise for the Creator. Sometimes this is </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e6 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws4f">expressed in language reminiscent of Genesis 1, other times the lan<span class="ws5">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e7 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws80">guage is more general; but in all cases, the description of Creation is </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e8 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws35">consistent with Genesis 1 and reminds us of the foundational role of </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4e9 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wse8">Genesis in our understanding of our origins as sons and daughters of </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4ea ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5">God.</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
